HEADWORD: Genesee epoch
<hw>Gen`e*see" ep"och</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>The
closing subdivision of the Hamilton period in the American Devonian
system; -- so called because the formations of this period crop out in
<xex>Genesee</xex>, New York.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Genesial</ent>⟦br⟧
